  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n`Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` option is disabled by default. And it's true for newly created user. However, once user re-login to account, this option auto-toggles in `ON` state. Even if to toggle it back into `OFF` -> relogin and `ON` again. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n`Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` -> `OFF` by default\r\n`Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` -> kept in `OFF` state after relogin UNTIL it's enabled into `ON` state\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n`Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled`  turns into ON state each time user relogins to account\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/120209600-8b3db900-c237-11eb-97ae-e6a8d147efed.mov\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open Status\r\n2) Create new account\r\n**Actual result = Expected result:** `Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` = `OFF`\r\n3) Re-login to account\r\n**Actual result:** `Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` = `ON`\r\n**Expected result:** `Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` = `OFF`\r\n4) Switch off communities by `Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` -> turn `OFF` toggle butoon\r\n5) Re-login to account\r\n**Actual result:** `Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` = `ON`\r\n**Expected result:** `Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Comunities enabled` = `OFF`\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
